  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite being set to publish in 2024, \"Knowledge and Practical Knowledge\" shows promise for future discourse in its field, supported by commercial linkages via platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads, indicating an anticipated interest from both academic and general audiences.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Knowledge and Practical Knowledge,\" set for publication by Peter Lang Verlag in 2024, is positioned to influence the conversation surrounding epistemology and practical knowledge. Although it has not yet garnered citations or community discussions on platforms like Wikipedia or Reddit, the work's anticipated impact is indicated by its strong commercial presence on sites such as Amazon and Goodreads.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The absence of early citations or community dialogue suggests that the book is still under the radar, yet the fact that it is listed on popular commercial platforms highlights an expectation of readership and interest. This may point towards an upcoming influence once it reaches wider academic and public audiences.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Even without extensive metrics to currently quantify its impact, the foundational concepts within \"Knowledge and Practical Knowledge\" may serve as a catalyst for future research and discussions in related disciplines. Its title implies a deep exploration of the intersection between knowledge theory and its practical applications, which could resonate with various fields including education, philosophy, and cognitive science.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">As the work prepares for its release, monitoring its uptake and discourse will be crucial in understanding how it contributes to the academic landscape and potentially induces further research trajectories in the realm of knowledge studies.</p>",
